==Japanese==
===Etymology===
Japanese [[か]] (''ka'') [question particle] + しら (''shira'') [the [[irrealis]] form of [[しる]] (''shiru''), "to know"]

===Particle===
[[Category:Japanese particles]]
'''かしら''' (''ka shira'')

# I wonder.
#: かしら (''ka shira'') is similar to [[かな]] (''ka na''), but is used more by women than by men.
#*　彼は[[怪しい]]人'''かしら'''。
#*:かれは[[あやしい]]ひと'''かしら'''。
#*:''Kare wa [[ayashii]] hito '''ka shira'''.''
#*:'''I wonder''' if he's a [[suspicious]] person.